    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const currentDate = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\nconst rawMessage = $json.content || '';\nconst safeMessage = rawMessage.replace(/\\\\/g, '\\\\\\\\').replace(/\"/g, '\\\\\"');\n\nconst prompt = `You are a calendar assistant. Analyze the following message and return ONLY valid JSON with no explanation.\n\nClassify the intent as one of: \"create\", \"delete\", \"unclear\", or \"ignore\".\n- \"create\": user wants to schedule or add a calendar event\n- \"delete\": user wants to remove or cancel a calendar event\n- \"unclear\": message seems calendar-related but lacks enough detail\n- \"ignore\": message is unrelated to calendar management\n\nIf intent is \"create\" or \"delete\", extract:\n- title: event name (string)\n- date: ISO 8601 date (YYYY-MM-DD), infer from relative terms like \"tomorrow\", \"Friday\"\n- time: 24h time string (HH:MM), or null if not specified\n- allDay: boolean, true only if no time is mentioned and the event is clearly a full-day event\n\nToday's date is ${currentDate} (ISO 8601 format).\n\nReturn format:\n{\"intent\": \"...\", \"title\": \"...\", \"date\": \"...\", \"time\": \"...\", \"allDay\": false}\n\nMessage: \"${safeMessage}\"`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { prompt } }];"
      },
      "id": "code-prompt",
      "name": "Build Prompt",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1120,
        368
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://localhost:11434/api/chat",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ model: 'llama3.2:latest', messages: [{ role: 'user', content: $json.prompt }], stream: false, format: 'json' }) }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "http-ollama",
      "name": "Call Ollama",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        1344,
        368
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const VALID_INTENTS = ['create', 'delete', 'unclear', 'ignore'];\n\nlet parsed;\ntry {\n  const content = $json.message?.content || $json.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || '';\n  parsed = typeof content === 'string' ? JSON.parse(content) : content;\n} catch (e) {\n  return [{ json: { intent: 'ignore', _parseError: true } }];\n}\n\nconst intent = parsed.intent;\nif (!VALID_INTENTS.includes(intent)) {\n  return [{ json: { intent: 'ignore', _invalidIntent: true } }];\n}\n\nif (intent === 'delete' && !parsed.date) {\n  return [{ json: { intent: 'unclear', _reason: 'delete_no_date' } }];\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: { ...parsed } }];"
      },
      "id": "code-parse",
      "name": "Parse Ollama Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
